1. For Loop
A for loop means we specify the condition how many times to do the task 
for (initialization; condition; update) {
}
for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
  System.out.println(i);
}



2. While Loop
A while loop is used when you don’t know how many times the loop goes,its depends on the condition
Syntax
while (condition) {
}
int i = 1;

while (i <= 5) {
  System.out.println(i);
  i++;
}
